@node MAIN "Welcome"

   @{b}popasl @{ub}PLUGIN

   Version: 1.2
   Date   : 10-Feb-1998


   PopAsl plugin can be used to pop up some kinds of standard system
   asl requesters. Using this asl popup plugin, you don't need to worry
   about handling asl requesters. The plugins will automatically open
   one when the popup button is pressed and update the corresponding
   string gadget when the user terminates the requester. From the
   programmers point of view, all you have to do is to handle the string
   gadgets contents.


   @{"Constructors/ Destructor" link POPASL_CONSTRUCTOR}
   @{"New Methods" link POPASL_METHODS}
   @{"Special Tags" link POPASL_TAGS}
   @{"Exceptions" link POPASL_EXCEPTIONS}
   @{"History" link POPASL_HISTORY}
   @{"ToDo" link POPASL_TODO}
   @{"Author" link AUTHOR}

@endnode

->>> POPASL_CONSTRUCTOR
@node POPASL_CONSTRUCTOR "Constuctors/ Destructor"

   @{BG shine}Constructor@{BG back}

      @{b}popasl(@{"tags" link POPASL_TAGS}:PTR TO tagitem)@{ub}

      For creating a new plugin object use for example:
      @{FG fill}
      DEF pa:PTR TO popasl_plugin
      NEW pa.popasl([..., TAG_DONE])
      @{FG text}


   @{BG shine}Destructor@{BG back}

      END *must* be called for each NEWed object.


@endnode
-><<

->>> POPASL_METHODS
@node POPASL_METHODS "New Methods"

   @{b}set(@{"tag" link POPASL_TAGS}, value)@{ub}

      By calling this method it's possible to change attributes
      at runtime. You can use all tags with the S flag set.
      This method can also be used before the GUI is created and when
      the window is closed.
      Value is a LONG and contains the argument for the used tag.
      @{FG fill}
      Example:
      DEF pa:PTR TO popasl_plugin
      ...
      NEW pa.popasl([PLA_PopAsl_Type, PLV_PopAsl_Type_Drawer, TAG_DONE])
      ...
      pa.set(PLA_PopAsl_Disabled, TRUE)
      ...
      @{FG text}

   @{b}value,check:=get(@{"tag" link POPASL_TAGS})@{ub}

      This method is the counterpart to set. All tags with G flag
      can be used. Argument is the tag you want to get. Return values
      are the requested value and as second a boolean value. So if
      check is FALSE the used tag can't be get.

      @{FG fill}...
      value,check:=pa.get(PLA_PopAsl_Disabled)
      ...@{FG text}

      After this:
       value=TRUE
       check=TRUE

      But if you try:

      @{FG fill}...
      value,check:=pa.get(PLA_PopAsl_Type)
      ...@{FG text}

      Then you get this:
       value:=-1
       check:=FALSE


@endnode
-><<

->>> POPASL_TAGS
@node POPASL_TAGS "Tags"
 The letters [ISG] show you when the tags can be used.
 I = @{"Initalisation" link POPASL_CONSTRUCTOR}
 S = @{"Set Method" link POPASL_METHODS}
 G = @{"Get Method" link POPASL_METHODS 18}


   @{FG shine}PLA_PopAsl_Disabled@{FG text}  [ISG]

      Disable or enable a gadget. Setting this tag causes the
      gadget to become disabled, it gets a ghost pattern and
      doesn't respond to user input any longer.


   @{FG shine}PLA_PopAsl_Type@{FG text}  [I..]

      This tag allows to set the type of asl requester. Pass one
      of the following values as tag value:

         PLV_PopAsl_Type_Drawer
         PLV_PopAsl_Type_File
         PLV_PopAsl_Type_Font

      If you pass a wrong value to this tag an @{"exception" link POPASL_EXCEPTIONS} will be raised.

      PopAsl plugin offers a standard handling for all types.
      When a file requester is opened, the plugin splits the string
      gadgets contents into a path and a file name and uses these as
      initial paremeters for the requester.
      Font popups translate a font into a name/size pair, e.g."topaz/8".
      If you don't set the size the default is 8.

      Default is set to PLV_PopAsl_Type_Drawer.


   @{FG shine}PLA_PopAsl_Contents@{FG text}  [ISG]

      Get and set a string gadgets contents. You may @{b}not@{ub} modify
      the returned string. If you want to use the string make a local copy.
      PLA_PopAsl_Contents gets updated every time when the contents of the
      string gadget change.
      Default is ''.


   @{FG shine}PLA_PopAsl_GadgetID@{FG text}  [I..]

      The gadget ID which will be passed to the created gadgets.
      You have to pass only one ID. The second one is calculated
      by adding 1 to the passed ID.
      By default the ID's a generated by the plugin itself. This
      ID's should be unique in nearly all cases. But to avoid problems
      you should set this tag.


   @{FG shine}PLA_PopAsl_ButtonText@{FG text}  [I..]

      String to be displayed in the button.

      Default are the following strings:

         Drawer: 'Path...'
         File  : 'File...'
         Font  : 'Font...'


   @{FG shine}PLA_PopAsl_ButtonOnRight@{FG text}  [I..]

      Set this to TRUE if you want to change the button position
      from left to right.
      Default is FALSE.


   @{FG shine}PLA_PopAsl_NoFontExtension@{FG text}  [I..]

      If you set this to TRUE the '.font' extension from the name
      will be removed after selecting from requester.

      topaz.font/8  ->  topaz/8


   @{FG shine}PLA_PopAsl_Title@{FG text}  [IS.]

      Set a user defined requester title.


   @{FG shine}PLA_PopAsl_UserData@{FG text}  [ISG]

      Handles the UserData field of this object.


@endnode
